"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Bulkeley was born in 1443, in Cheadle, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Richard Bulkeley, was 26 and his mother, Alice Bostock, was 24. He married Ellen Griffith in 1468, in Alverstoke, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1490, in Beaumaris, Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 47."},"et":{"1443–1490":"1443–1490","1443–1485":"1443–1485","1445–Female":"1445–Surnud","1471–1555":"1471–1555","1417–1500":"1417–1500","1419–1485":"1419–1485","1468":"1468","1500":"1500","1555":"1555","1445":"1445","1443":"1443","1442":"1442","1485":"1485","1471":"1471","1419":"1419","1490":"1490","1417":"1417","Alverstoke, Hampshire, England":"Alverstoke, Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","St Mary Beaumaris, Anglesey, Wales":"Beaumaris, Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom","Radnorshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Radnorshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Cheadle, Cheshire, England":"Cheadle, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1443–1490":"1443–1490","1443–1485":"1443–1485","1445–Female":"1445–Kuollut","1471–1555":"1471–1555","1417–1500":"1417–1500","1419–1485":"1419–1485","1468":"1468","1500":"1500","1555":"1555","1445":"1445","1443"